<https://w3id.org/FAIROS/metric/FAIROS-A1-02> a dqv:Metric ;
    dcterms:identifier <https://w3id.org/FAIROS/metric/FAIROS-A1-02> ;
    dcterms:title "Metadata is accessible through a standardized communication protocol"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "FAIROS-metric-A1-02"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "FAIROS-metric-A1-02"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:description """This metric ensures that metadata is accessible using standardized communication protocols that support interoperability and automated retrieval.

**What is being measured?**

Whether the metadata from the Research Object can be retrieved using a standardized, open, and well-documented communication protocol, such as HTTP, HTTPS, OAI-PMH, SPARQL, or REST APIs.

**Why should we measure it?**

When metadata is exposed through widely adopted protocols, it ensures that systems and tools—regardless of platform—can automatically access and exchange metadata. 

**What must be provided for the measurement?**

The endpoint where the metadata can be accessed.

**What are considered valid results?**

The metadata is accessible using a standardized communication protocol (e.g., HTTP, HTTPS, OAI-PMH, SPARQL, FTP, REST)."""^^xsd:string ;
